  "textSourceURL": "https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/11339",
  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 1.74,
      "end": 7.44,
      "text": "This is a labor box recording. All labor box recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 8.34,
      "end": 12.9,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit laborbox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.78,
      "end": 17.28,
      "text": "Recorded by Patty McCoy in Hudson, Colorado.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 19.38,
      "end": 20.64,
      "text": "ASAP's fable.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.7,
      "end": 23.6,
      "text": "The stag with one eye.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.6,
      "end": 32.94,
      "text": "A stag, blind of one eye, was grazing close to the seashore and kept his sound eye turned towards the land,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 33.52,
      "end": 37.02,
      "text": "so as to be able to perceive the approach of the hounds.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 37.66,
      "end": 45.82,
      "text": "While the blind eye, he turned towards the sea, never suspecting that any danger would threaten him from that quarter.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 45.82,
      "end": 57.72,
      "text": "As it fell out, however, some sailors coasting along the shore, spied him, and shot an arrow at him by which he was mortally wounded.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 58.46,
      "end": 68.22,
      "text": "As he lay dying, he said to himself, rich that I am, I bethought me of the dangers of the land, when none assailed me,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 68.92,
      "end": 74.52,
      "text": "but I feared dull peril from the sea, yet thence has come my ruin.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 75.18,
      "end": 81.78,
      "text": "This forced off on the sails as from an unexpected quarter, end of the stag with one eye.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
